866
00:56:36.426 --> 00:56:38.546
Did you know I was gonna
be in the graveyard that day?

867
00:56:38.996 --> 00:56:40.106
- How would I have known that?
- I dunno.

868
00:56:40.130 --> 00:56:41.730
Why didn't you just
tell me who you were?

869
00:56:42.599 --> 00:56:45.569
Look. it's like six degrees of
separation. It's not a big deal.

870
00:56:45.969 --> 00:56:47.249
Well. then. why did you hide it?

871
00:56:47.304 --> 00:56:49.449
- Well. I wasn't trying to hide it.
- Just stop the car.

872
00:56:49.473 --> 00:56:50.771
- Come on.
- Please stop the car.

873
00:56:58.682 --> 00:57:01.516
Joanie. you're overreacting.
Nothing has changed.

874
00:57:01.585 --> 00:57:04.817
I'm still the same person I
was 30 seconds ago in that car.

875
00:57:04.888 --> 00:57:05.888
You lied to me.

876
00:57:05.923 --> 00:57:09.291
I didn't lie. I just didn't
tell you the whole story.

877
00:57:09.359 --> 00:57:10.470
And you didn't tell
me the whole story.

878
00:57:10.494 --> 00:57:13.259
You've been married this
whole time. I mean. come on.

879
00:57:15.132 --> 00:57:16.532
