understood each other.

880
00:57:16.733 --> 00:57:18.292
What is it you thought
you understood?

881
00:57:18.368 --> 00:57:19.961
That we're not sheep.

882
00:57:20.837 --> 00:57:22.499
That we both play
by different rules.

883
00:57:25.375 --> 00:57:27.867
This is stupid. I can't
go to Vienna with you.

884
00:57:28.278 --> 00:57:30.372
- Why not?
- We were just fucking. EJ.

885
00:57:30.447 --> 00:57:31.278
that's all it was.

886
00:57:31.348 --> 00:57:33.579
Why are you trying to
turn it into something else?

887
00:57:33.884 --> 00:57:36.547
Are you really so desperate
for someone to love?

888
00:57:39.289 --> 00:57:40.484
I guess I am.

889
00:57:42.926 --> 00:57:46.021
What are you even doing here? Why
are you so obsessed with my family?

890
00:57:46.096 --> 00:57:48.622
Is it some sort of
transitive whore property?

891
00:57:48.699 --> 00:57:49.530
What?

892
00:57:49.666 --> 00:57:52.465
Your mother and my mother
both fucked over the same woman.

893
00:57:52.536 --> 00:57:53.868
My mother and
Helen were friends.

894
00:57:53.937 --> 00:57:54.937
Right.

895
00:57:55.672 --> 00:57:57.163
Helen was like a
second mother to me.

896
00:57:57.240 --> 00:57:59.539
There-there is such
a thing as forgiveness.

897
00:57:59.609 --> 00:58:02.135
I realize that that's completely
out of your frame of reference.

898
00:58:02.212 --> 00:58:04.841
but there are certain people
who are actually capable of it.

899
00:58:05.015 --> 00:58:08.008
And believe it or not. this place
was part of my childhood. too.

900
00:58:08.385 --> 00:58:10.445
My mother and I came out here

901
00:58:10.520 --> 00:58:12.398
and stayed with Helen's
parents when I was young.

902
00:58:12.422 --> 00:58:14.342
