You have to understand.
Joanie. your father was...

954
01:01:59.983 --> 01:02:01.975
carrying a tremendous
amount of pain.

955
01:02:03.520 --> 01:02:05.580
Sounds like you cared about him.

956
01:02:05.889 --> 01:02:09.291
Well. "cared" is a
strong word. I mean...

957
01:02:10.060 --> 01:02:11.892
No. I respected Cole.

958
01:02:13.663 --> 01:02:17.794
I think. under the circumstances.
that's the most one could expect.

959
01:02:20.003 --> 01:02:22.131
How long have you
been back in Montauk?

960
01:02:22.939 --> 01:02:25.170
I moved back here after my
oldest daughter's wedding.

961
01:02:25.242 --> 01:02:28.303
which was 30 years ago now.

962
01:02:28.912 --> 01:02:30.778
- That's when we left.
- I know.

963
01:02:31.047 --> 01:02:35.280
And the day Cole came back into
town. he walked through that door and...

964
01:02:36.186 --> 01:02:39.384
I think both of us nearly
had a heart attack.

965
01:02:42.158 --> 01:02:46.789
But time has a habit of making these.
these big things seem small somehow.

966
01:02:49.866 --> 01:02:51.596
It's so good to see you. Joanie.

967
01:02:52.335 --> 01:02:54.463
It really is so good to see you.

968
01:02:55.305 --> 01:02:57.604
Tell me about your life.
What-what do you. uh...

969
01:02:58.441 --> 01:02:59.500
What do you do?

970
01:03:00.277 --> 01:03:01.802
I'm a coastal engineer.

971
01:03:02.812 --> 01:03:04.610
I'm trying to save the
world from drowning.

972
01:03:05.548 --> 01:03:06.548
Really?

973
01:03:08.718 --> 01:03:10.983
- Do you have any children?
- Two.

974
01:03:12.022 --> 01:03:13.251
Boys or girls?

975
01:03:13.857 --> 01:03:14.857
Daughters.

976
01:03:15.458 --> 01:03:17.427
Thea and Madeline.

977
01:03:17.494 --> 01:03:19.019
That's wonderful. Joanie.

978
01:03:20.530 --> 01:03:21.530
But...

979
01:03:22.799 --> 01:03:24.859
I can only love them
when I'm away from them.

980
01:03:25.902 --> 01:03:28.201
When I'm away from
them. I miss them terribly.

981
01:03:28.705 --> 01:03:30.401
But when I'm
with them. I can't...

982
01:03:32.776 --> 01:03:34.870
I can't even hold them
and I don't know why.

983
01:03:40.016 --> 01:03:42.042
I have this friend
who's a. uh...

984
01:03:43.086 --> 01:03:44.918
He's an epigeneticist.

985
01:03:46.289 --> 01:03:50.021
And he has a theory about
trauma being passed down.

986
01:03:50.427 --> 01:03:51.486
What's his name?

987
01:03:51.828 --> 01:03:55.230
Uh. Eddie. He's like a. he's
kind of like a. a nephew of mine.

988
01:03:56.666 --> 01:03:57.666
Fascinating.

989
01:03:57.801 --> 01:03:58.666
Go on.

990
01:03:58.735 --> 01:04:02.866
Well. he says that trauma can be
passed from one generation to another.

991
01:04:03.873 --> 01:04:06.274
That it actually
changes the DNA.

992
01:04:07.477 --> 01:04:09.878
And he says there
are studies where. uh...

993
01:04:10.780 --> 01:04:13.978
where there are rats who...

994
01:04:16.386 --> 01:04:20.824
who are shocked every time
they. uh. smell cherry blossom.

995
01:04:22.025 --> 01:04:23.891
And then they breed the rats

996
01:04:24.027 --> 01:04:27.930
and their babies are
afraid of cherry blossom.

997
01:04:29.032 --> 01:04:30.762
Wow. Amazing.

998
01:04:30.834 --> 01:04:33.633
Anyway. my point is that your
parents went through a lot of trauma.

999
01:04:33.703 --> 01:04:35.968
They... I mean.
they lost a child.

1000
01:04:36.039 --> 01:04:39.874
So it would make sense that
you. too. were afraid of loss.

1001
01:04:41.678 --> 01:04:44.443
And maybe even
a bit paralyzed by it.

1002
01:04:45.215 --> 01:04:46.726
Yeah. no. I know a
bit about that theory.

1003
01:04:46.750 --> 01:04:48.427
There's a question
about whether the children

1004
01:04:48.451 --> 01:04:51.114
of trauma survivors also
inherit their resilience.

1005
01:04:51.788 --> 01:04:53.120
Oh. I didn't know that.

1006
01:04:54.124 --> 01:04:55.524
That's wonderful.

1007
01:04:55.959 --> 01:04:58.986
So maybe you inherited
her resilience as well.

1008
01:04:59.195 --> 01:05:00.823
You mean his resilience.

1009
01:05:01.431 --> 01:05:03.093
No. no. no. I mean hers.

1010
01:05:03.600 --> 01:05:06.331
No. No offense to Cole.
but he-he never changed.

1011
01:05:06.836 --> 01:05:11.001
I mean. your mother always said that
Cole used to run away from his problems.

1012
01:05:11.608 --> 01:05:13.907
But Alison. she was
always working on herself.

1013
01:05:13.977 --> 01:05:16.173
She was a work in
progress and she knew it.

1014
01:05:16.746 --> 01:05:18.237
She was so present.

1015
01:05:19.649 --> 01:05:22.312
Feeling everything
so deeply and...

1016
01:05:23.853 --> 01:05:26.755
She made herself stay
awake and was so disappointed

1017
01:05:26.823 --> 01:05:30.191
when other people seem

1018
01:05:31.261 --> 01:05:33.127
so asleep in their lives.

1019
01:05:34.364 --> 01:05:36.560
Noah. when I was four years old.

1020
01:05:36.633 --> 01:05:40.331
she dumped me on Cole and
Luisa's doorstep and took off.

1021
01:05:40.403 --> 01:05:41.496
To get help.

1022
01:05:42.639 --> 01:05:46.007
And then. six months later. she came
back and she fought your father in court.

1023
01:05:46.242 --> 01:05:47.266
No. she didn't.

1024
01:05:47.343 --> 01:05:48.777
You-you don't know this?

1025
01:05:48.845 --> 01:05:52.407
I thought they just
let her have me back

1026
01:05:52.482 --> 01:05:54.508
because they felt sorry for her.

1027
01:05:54.918 --> 01:05:56.284
No. Joanie. no. no.

1028
01:05:56.352 --> 01:05:59.447
Cole and Luisa tried
to keep you from her.

1029
01:05:59.756 --> 01:06:01.486
She had to humiliate herself.

1030
01:06:01.558 --> 01:06:04.357
It was devastating. You...
They never told you this?

1031
01:06:05.929 --> 01:06:07.454
Oh. Jesus Christ.

1032
01:06:09.966 --> 01:06:12.265
Joanie. it's very
important you know this:

1033
01:06:12.669 --> 01:06:14.604
you were her whole life.

1034
01:06:15.572 --> 01:06:17.700
Everything she
did. she did for you.

1035
01:06:19.409 --> 01:06:22.277
She tried to get help so that
she could be there for you.

1036
01:06:23.947 --> 01:06:27.281
She was trying to give you
a better life than she had.

1037
01:06:27.350 --> 01:06:28.978
and she was succeeding.

1038
01:06:32.188 --> 01:06:33.247
You know. she's...

1039
01:06:35.058 --> 01:06:38.756
she's one of the only people I've
ever met in my whole life who...

1040
01:06:39.562 --> 01:06:41.827
who actually managed to change.

1041
01:06:43.433 --> 01:06:45.273
When I met her. she
was this shell of a person.

1042
01:06:45.301 --> 01:06:47.861
and by the time she
died. she had a job

1043
01:06:48.371 --> 01:06:50.135
helping other people

1044
01:06:50.940 --> 01:06:54.104
heal from the same
trauma that she had and...

1045
01:06:55.678 --> 01:06:57.476
Do you know how
difficult that is?

1046
01:06:59.315 --> 01:07:01.443
How few people
actually achieve that?

1047
01:07:02.252 --> 01:07:04.278
She was still
dating married men.

1048
01:07:06.189 --> 01:07:09.819
Oh. she didn't know he was married.
What-what happened with Ben. that...

1049
01:07:10.326 --> 01:07:11.760
that was not her fault.

1050
01:07:13.463 --> 01:07:15.432
Well. what good did it do her?

1051
01:07:17.400 --> 01:07:19.460
All those changes?

1052
01:07:22.705 --> 01:07:24.435
- He killed her anyway.
- Joanie.

1053
01:07:25.909 --> 01:07:29.175
if the lesson you're taking away
from your mother's death is not to try.

1054
01:07:29.245 --> 01:07:31.476
then that's a great.
great tragedy.

1055
01:07:32.782 --> 01:07:34.273
Change is hard.

1056
01:07:36.319 --> 01:07:37.378
It takes a long time.

1057
01:07:37.453 --> 01:07:39.945
Sometimes more than a lifetime.

1058
01:07:40.823 --> 01:07:42.291
What the fuck does that mean?

1059
01:07:45.395 --> 01:07:49.196
Sometimes we can
only start journeys

1060
01:07:50.466 --> 01:07:53.265
that our children
have to finish for us.

1061
01:07:55.672 --> 01:07:57.163
It's too late to
hear those things.

1062
01:07:57.674 --> 01:07:59.472
- It's not too late.
- Yes. it is.

1063
01:07:59.542 --> 01:08:01.204
I've already screwed it all up.

1064
01:08:02.445 --> 01:08:04.471
I can't go off with someone new.

1065
01:08:04.881 --> 01:08:06.406
And I can't go home.

1066
01:08:07.417 --> 01:08:12.048
So. instead. I'm fucking
stuck here in some sort of...

1067
01:08:12.922 --> 01:08:14.948
seafood purgatory...

1068
01:08:17.060 --> 01:08:18.289
talking to you.

1069
01:08:18.361 --> 01:08:21.058
Why can't you go home?

1070
01:08:24.667 --> 01:08:27.694
Why don't you tell me. Noah?
You seem to know a lot. Why...

1071
01:08:29.172 --> 01:08:30.663
Why can't I go home?

1072
01:08:33.009 --> 01:08:34.705
Well. maybe 'cause it's hard.

1073
01:08:35.612 --> 01:08:37.205
Going home is hard.

1074
01:08:38.982 --> 01:08:40.541
Staying with someone.

1075
01:08:41.751 --> 01:08:43.515
loving them no matter what.

1076
01:08:45.521 --> 01:08:46.614
that's hard.

1077
01:08:47.924 --> 01:08:49.222
It's so easy to...

1078
01:08:51.160 --> 01:08:52.856
go find someone new.

1079
01:08:54.130 --> 01:08:55.962
reinvent yourself in their eyes.

1080
01:08:56.032 --> 01:08:58.524
and try once more
to live without flaw.

1081
01:08:58.601 --> 01:09:00.365
but sooner or later you realize

1082
01:09:00.436 --> 01:09:02.302
the only thing you're
running from is death.

1083
01:09:04.107 --> 01:09:06.508
It's not another
person at all. it's...

1084
01:09:07.744 --> 01:09:09.076
it's death. and...

1085
01:09:10.947 --> 01:09:13.246
when that finally
occurs to you. you...

1086
01:09:15.618 --> 01:09:18.884
you yearn more than anything
for someone who really knows you.

1087
01:09:22.425 --> 01:09:24.417
Who really knows
every inch of you.

1088
01:09:26.529 --> 01:09:28.555
And will remember
you when you're gone.

1089
01:09:32.835 --> 01:09:34.428
What are you trying to say?

1090
01:09:35.004 --> 01:09:36.324
What I'm trying
to say is that...

1091
01:09:37.740 --> 01:09:40.608
if... if trauma and pain

1092
01:09:41.110 --> 01:09:44.342
can echo through
generations. then so can love.

1093
01:09:47.817 --> 01:09:52.187
If abandonment can
ripple across time.

1094
01:09:52.255 --> 01:09:55.225
then so can presence.

1095
01:09:57.360 --> 01:09:59.989
I mean. you-you've suffered
a lot of loss in your life. Joanie.

1096
01:10:00.063 --> 01:10:02.430
but you've also
had a lot of love.

1097
01:10:06.602 --> 01:10:10.539
And you may not be
able to save the Earth.

1098
01:10:12.442 --> 01:10:14.377
But you can be
there for your children.

1099
01:10:15.511 --> 01:10:16.979
No matter what happens.

1100
01:10:35.364 --> 01:10:38.698
<i>♪ Same clothes the last time ♪</i>

1101
01:10:38.768 --> 01:10:40.999
<i>♪ You disappointed me ♪</i>

1102
01:10:42.472 --> 01:10:46.568
<i>♪ I've got those same
clothes The last time ♪</i>

1103
01:10:46.642 --> 01:10:49.407
<i>♪ You disappointed me ♪</i>

1104
01:10:51.314 --> 01:10:54.375
Don't tell anyone.
but I miss Dad.

1105
01:10:54.984 --> 01:10:56.043
Yeah.

1106
01:10:58.788 --> 01:11:00.984
Where do you
think he is tonight?

1107
01:11:01.290 --> 01:11:02.290
He's here.

1108
01:11:03.192 --> 01:11:06.890
- What do you mean? He's here?
- No. no. He's in Montauk. I think.

1109
01:11:07.263 --> 01:11:08.629
At least he was this morning.

1110
01:11:09.265 --> 01:11:11.564
- Why?
- We rehearsed your flash mob.

1111
01:11:11.701 --> 01:11:12.794
Martin.

1112
01:11:13.669 --> 01:11:15.429
I don't think you were
supposed to know that.

1113
01:11:25.381 --> 01:11:27.680
How could you not tell
me he was in Montauk?

1114
01:11:28.751 --> 01:11:29.844
He told us not to.

1115
01:11:30.353 --> 01:11:31.553
He thought it would upset you.

1116
01:11:31.721 --> 01:11:35.158
But he had to be here. He
basically planned the entire wedding.

1117
01:11:35.391 --> 01:11:36.835
I thought Mom took over
the wedding planning.

1118
01:11:36.859 --> 01:11:37.986
She told me she would.

1119
01:11:38.261 --> 01:11:42.528
No. I think maybe you told
her that she was going to.

1120
01:11:42.665 --> 01:11:45.010
Look. it was a group
effort. and we all pitched in.

1121
01:11:45.034 --> 01:11:48.074
Yeah. I don't know why you're so upset.
I think it came together really well.

1122
01:11:48.171 --> 01:11:50.048
What. so he's just
somewhere by himself right now

1123
01:11:50.072 --> 01:11:51.563
while we're all
enjoying the party?

1124
01:11:51.707 --> 01:11:53.185
Well. you said you
didn't want him here.

1125
01:11:53.209 --> 01:11:55.144
Where the fuck is
he even staying?

1126
01:11:55.411 --> 01:11:56.674
At the Memory Motel.

1127
01:11:56.979 --> 01:11:59.358
Of course you know that. Stacey.
You're such a fucking daddy's girl.

1128
01:11:59.382 --> 01:12:01.044
Hey. She's 12.

1129
01:12:01.350 --> 01:12:03.581
Look. I just think
it's really awful

1130
01:12:03.653 --> 01:12:05.573
that none of you told me
that he was coming here.

1131
01:12:06.189 --> 01:12:09.921
- As if I'm the crazy one. like...
- We don't think you're crazy. Whit.

1132
01:12:10.159 --> 01:12:13.220
We just wanted you to have a
good day. All of us. him included.

1133
01:12:13.296 --> 01:12:14.730
How could you let him come here?

1134
01:12:14.797 --> 01:12:17.198
I thought you understood.
You of all people.

1135
01:12:17.266 --> 01:12:18.859
I do understand.

1136
01:12:19.035 --> 01:12:22.631
Your father's made some real mistakes
and you've had to bear the brunt of them.

1137
01:12:22.705 --> 01:12:24.230
But he does love you. Whit.

1138
01:12:24.340 --> 01:12:26.138
And he wanted
to do this for you.

1139
01:12:26.542 --> 01:12:28.443
Even if he couldn't
be here to see it.

1140
01:12:38.621 --> 01:12:41.113
Yeah. He's got you all fooled.

1141
01:12:42.758 --> 01:12:44.556
He bought my
mother a plane ticket.

1142
01:12:45.962 --> 01:12:47.260
He didn't have to do that.

1143
01:12:49.765 --> 01:12:50.765
He did?

1144
01:12:56.272 --> 01:12:58.241
- Fuck.
- Excuse me.

1145
01:12:58.674 --> 01:13:00.267
Could I get a dance
with the bride?

1146
01:13:01.777 --> 01:13:02.904
Of course. Grandpa.

1147
01:13:27.069 --> 01:13:29.595
What's wrong. kiddo?

1148
01:13:29.939 --> 01:13:32.499
You're awfully perceptive
for someone with dementia.

1149
01:13:32.842 --> 01:13:35.505
Well. this is a good day.

1150
01:13:38.681 --> 01:13:40.309
So tell me. what's on your mind?

1151
01:13:41.183 --> 01:13:43.175
It's your wedding day.
You don't look happy.

1152
01:13:44.220 --> 01:13:45.950
Sometimes I don't
know what to think.

1153
01:13:46.255 --> 01:13:47.255
About what?

1154
01:13:47.556 --> 01:13:50.788
If people hurt you very badly.
do you have to forgive them?

1155
01:13:52.228 --> 01:13:53.228
No.

1156
01:13:54.864 --> 01:13:58.323
But sometimes it hurts you more
than it hurts them to hold a grudge.

1157
01:14:00.536 --> 01:14:02.266
What's it all for. then?

1158
01:14:03.739 --> 01:14:06.004
If people can act however
they want and get forgiven.

1159
01:14:06.075 --> 01:14:09.011
then what is the point of trying
to be good in the first place?

1160
01:14:11.547 --> 01:14:13.982
I think it's about what
kind of life you want to live.

1161
01:14:15.551 --> 01:14:19.955
You will have plenty of
opportunities to be angry in your life.

1162
01:14:20.856 --> 01:14:23.121
You have less chance
to love people. though.

1163
01:14:23.526 --> 01:14:24.755
Really love them.

1164
01:14:25.294 --> 01:14:26.294
So you just...

1165
01:14:28.197 --> 01:14:31.167
you want to be careful how many
of those opportunities you squander.

1166
01:14:32.568 --> 01:14:35.197
I think young people believe
they'll just keep coming.

1167
01:14:35.271 --> 01:14:37.797
but they don't.

1168
01:14:53.055 --> 01:14:55.024
Grandpa. can you
help me with something?

1169
01:14:56.959 --> 01:14:58.325
Anything for you.

1170
01:15:04.834 --> 01:15:07.668
You really think
he's gonna do it?

1171
01:15:07.737 --> 01:15:10.468
- He said he would.
- What if he forgets?

1172
01:15:10.539 --> 01:15:12.474
He was totally
lucid a moment ago.

1173
01:15:12.541 --> 01:15:14.286
It seems really dangerous.
He has Alzheimer's.

1174
01:15:14.310 --> 01:15:15.921
Do you have a better way
to sneak out of this wedding?

1175
01:15:15.945 --> 01:15:17.106
We can just walk out.

1176
01:15:17.179 --> 01:15:18.738
She can't. you
idiot. She's the bride.

1177
01:15:18.814 --> 01:15:20.934
Oh. my God. here he
comes. Okay. okay. Um...

1178
01:15:21.484 --> 01:15:22.884
Do we know the plan? Cake knife?

1179
01:15:22.952 --> 01:15:24.648
- Check.
- Platter?

1180
01:15:24.720 --> 01:15:25.847
- Yeah. Check.
- Okay.

1181
01:15:34.163 --> 01:15:35.529
Whoa!

1182
01:15:35.598 --> 01:15:38.397
Oh. my God. Bruce!

1183
01:15:40.036 --> 01:15:42.733
Bruce!

1184
01:15:42.805 --> 01:15:45.639
- No! Okay. Go. go. go. go.
- Okay.

1185
01:15:50.413 --> 01:15:51.413
Go find your sister.

1186
01:15:51.447 --> 01:15:52.710
Let's go. let's go. let's go.

1187
01:15:56.652 --> 01:15:57.779
I love you so much.

1188
01:16:00.656 --> 01:16:04.889
<i>♪ I might be old. but
I'm someone new ♪</i>

1189
01:16:04.960 --> 01:16:06.053
<i>♪ She said... ♪</i>

1190
01:16:06.128 --> 01:16:07.323
I found champagne!

1191
01:16:07.396 --> 01:16:08.440
I got the coats!

1192
01:16:08.464 --> 01:16:11.764
<i>♪ ...I could cry always ♪</i>

1193
01:16:11.834 --> 01:16:16.829
<i>♪ In the night. lay
your tired arms ♪</i>

1194
01:16:17.873 --> 01:16:20.104
<i>♪ She will have her way ♪</i>

1195
01:16:20.409 --> 01:16:23.277
- Shh.
- Are we sure about this?

1196
01:16:23.345 --> 01:16:26.873
<i>♪ ... believe her ♪</i>

1197
01:16:27.249 --> 01:16:28.249
Come on.

1198
01:16:30.686 --> 01:16:33.656
<i>♪ She's the life I've
been frightened of ♪</i>

1199
01:16:33.722 --> 01:16:34.883
Go. go. go.

1200
01:16:36.225 --> 01:16:39.923
<i>♪ Deathly silence And
especially the dark ♪</i>

1201
01:16:40.262 --> 01:16:42.959
<i>♪ Feels like I am heavy ♪</i>

1202
01:16:43.032 --> 01:16:44.694
<i>♪ And my spirit has died... ♪</i>

1203
01:16:45.134 --> 01:16:46.411
- Everyone stop! Back up!
- Whoa.

1204
01:16:46.435 --> 01:16:47.960
- Back up!
- Jesus Christ.

1205
01:16:48.037 --> 01:16:50.006
- What is it?
- What is going on?

1206
01:16:50.072 --> 01:16:51.870
- Mom is in there.
- So?

1207
01:16:53.309 --> 01:16:54.538
Oh. my God.

1208
01:16:55.277 --> 01:16:56.438
Oh. my God.

1209
01:16:56.879 --> 01:16:59.439
Oh. my God.

1210
01:17:00.382 --> 01:17:02.180
- Nice.
- This is so difficult.

1211
01:17:02.251 --> 01:17:04.516
- What do we do?
- I don't know. Whit.

1212
01:17:12.361 --> 01:17:16.799
<i>♪ Do. do. do. do. do. do ♪</i>

1213
01:17:16.866 --> 01:17:20.030
<i>♪ Do. do. do ♪</i>

1214
01:17:20.102 --> 01:17:23.402
